cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.LG 

The paper deals with the problem of inducing social networks from content exchanged across network edges, which is a problem in natural language processing and computational linguistics. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with social networks and their properties, which suggests that it could belong to cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks). The paper also uses unsupervised learning techniques, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with triadic features and structural balance, which suggests that it could belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing).
